## 3. PROJECT STATE — INBOUND LEAD FOLLOW-UP CADENCE REDESIGN

### One-line frame
Replace the voice-only inbound cadence with a multi-channel SMS + voice + email cadence, source-aware and persona-aware, with a global kill switch on any reply.

### The problem (quantified)
- **~80% of inbound leads never connect on first dial.**
- Current cadence: **22 dials in first 9 days, then 1/day perpetually.** Voice only.
- **No SMS layer. No email layer. No channel variation. No persona switching.**
- Voice is the channel consumers avoid; SMS is the channel they prefer (≈98% open / 45% reply).
- Result: leads that would text back are buried under voicemails, RRS gets marked spam, lost revenue is invisible because these prospects never enter a CRM stage.

### Lead sources in scope (cadence must differ by source)
- **Third-party aggregator leads** — fastest, most aggressive (shared with competitors, speed-to-lead is everything)
- **Web form / website inquiries** — fast, but warmer (intent already declared)
- **Google Local Services Ads (LSA)** — high-intent, often phone-first
- **Facebook / Meta lead forms** — colder, slower-burn, expect lower intent
- **Referrals and call-ins** — softer touch, persona = owner/manager early, never aggressive

### Design principles (non-negotiable)
- **Multi-channel:** SMS + voice + email, each channel doing what it does best.
- **State-aware kill switch:** ANY reply on ANY channel halts ALL outbound automation immediately. Global, not per-channel.
- **Persona-aware:** cadence transitions CSR → owner/manager at the right point (later touches, referrals, recovery attempts).
- **Compliance-first:** 10DLC, TCPA opt-in language on every web form, instant opt-out on any negative-intent signal (not just keyword "STOP").
- **Source-aware pacing.**
- **Cash-flow aware build:** MVP first, prove it, then expand.

### Deliverables (the six required outputs)
1. **Lead source audit** — origin, current connect rate, current handling per source.
2. **Multi-channel cadence design** — matrix of source × day × channel × persona × message.
3. **System architecture** — n8n workflows, Heymarket integration, Salesforce data model, Aircall coordination, kill-switch logic.
4. **Compliance setup** — 10DLC registration plan, web form consent language, opt-out detection (keyword + intent), DNC handling.
5. **Phased implementation plan** — MVP → full rollout, with success criteria per phase.
6. **PM handoff document** — buildable by an implementer without Brett in the room.

### Architectural decisions already locked
- **n8n is the orchestrator.** All cadence state machines live there.
- **Salesforce is system of record.** Lead object + custom fields for `Cadence_Status__c`, `Cadence_Source__c`, `Last_Channel__c`, `Kill_Switch__c`, `Opt_Out__c`, `Persona_Stage__c` (names indicative, not final).
- **Heymarket = SMS execution layer + shared inbox.** Inbound replies webhook → n8n → Salesforce update + kill switch.
- **Aircall = voice execution layer.** Cadence triggers dial tasks; call dispositions write back to Salesforce via existing integration.
- **Email = Google Workspace via n8n** (SMTP or Gmail API), tracked back to the Lead record.
- **Kill switch is centralized in n8n**, not duplicated per channel — single source of truth, reused by Unsold Estimate Rehash later.
- **Custom objects designed for reuse** across cadence projects (inbound follow-up now, unsold rehash next).

### Open questions / decisions still needed
- Exact day/channel matrix per source (to be designed in deliverable #2).
- Hand-off trigger from CSR persona → owner/manager persona (proposed: day 4–5 with no engagement, or after 2 ignored SMS).
- Cold-file definition (proposed: 14 days no engagement on aggregator/web, 21 days on Meta, 30 days on referral).
- Whether to layer a lightweight AI text agent for first-touch SMS triage, or keep all SMS human-sent from Heymarket in MVP. **Default for MVP: human-sent templates from Heymarket, AI triage in Phase 2.**
- 10DLC brand/campaign registration timeline — gating factor for SMS go-live.

### Risks / second-order effects to track
- **10DLC approval lag** can delay SMS launch 2–4 weeks. Start registration on day 1.
- **Heymarket shared inbox discipline** — if reps reply from personal phones, kill switch breaks. Enforce: all SMS through Heymarket, period.
- **Aircall + n8n race conditions** — if a dial is queued and a text reply lands mid-cadence, kill switch must beat the dialer. Solve with n8n-side queue check before each Aircall trigger, not after.
- **CSR capacity** — multi-channel doubles inbound reply volume into Heymarket. CSR may need a response SLA and/or AI-assisted draft replies sooner than Phase 2.
- **Source attribution drift** — if Salesforce `Lead_Source__c` is dirty, source-aware cadence routes wrong. Audit lead source data integrity as part of deliverable #1.
- **TCPA exposure on referrals/call-ins** — these often lack documented consent. Cadence for referrals should rely on call + email, with SMS only after explicit opt-in.
- **Forward-compat with Unsold Estimate Rehash** — any custom object or kill-switch logic built here must be namespaced for reuse, not hardcoded to "inbound."

### MVP definition (Phase 1 target)
- One source live end-to-end: **aggregator leads** (highest volume, highest pain).
- SMS + voice only (email Phase 2).
- Single persona (CSR) for MVP; persona switching Phase 2.
- Kill switch fully functional across SMS + voice.
- 10DLC registered and approved.
- Salesforce custom fields deployed and writing correctly.
- Success metric: connect rate on aggregator leads improves from current baseline (TBD in audit) by ≥30% within 30 days of go-live.

### Phase 2+
- Add web form, LSA, Meta, referral cadences.
- Add email channel.
- Add persona switching (CSR → owner/manager).
- Add AI-assisted SMS drafting in Heymarket for CSR.
- Bridge to Unsold Estimate Rehash project on shared infrastructure.

